From: Stefan Metzmacher <metze@samba.org>
Date: Thu, 18 Sep 2025 03:06:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] smb: client: fix smbdirect_recv_io leak in smbd_negotiate()
 error path
Git-commit: daac51c7032036a0ca5f1aa419ad1b0471d1c6e0
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc7
References: CVE-2025-39929 bsc#1251036

During tests of another unrelated patch I was able to trigger this
Error: Objects remaining on __kmem_cache_shutdown()

Cc: Steve French <smfrench@gmail.com>
Cc: Tom Talpey <tom@talpey.com>
Cc: Long Li <longli@microsoft.com>
Cc: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>
Cc: linux-cifs@vger.kernel.org
Cc: samba-technical@lists.samba.org
Fixes: f198186aa9bb ("CIFS: SMBD: Establish SMB Direct connection")
Signed-off-by: Stefan Metzmacher <metze@samba.org>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 fs/cifs/smbdirect.c |    4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/cifs/smbdirect.c
+++ b/fs/cifs/smbdirect.c
@@ -1092,8 +1092,10 @@ static int smbd_negotiate(struct smbd_co
 		"iov.lkey=0x%x\n",
 		rc, response->sge.addr,
 		response->sge.length, response->sge.lkey);
-	if (rc)
+	if (rc) {
+		put_receive_buffer(info, response);
 		return rc;
+	}
 
 	init_completion(&info->negotiate_completion);
 	info->negotiate_done = false;
